Ad Text:
Key influencing role

High growth property group

$140k - $150k + Super + Bonus

This property group, helmed by high profile individuals with years of experience in the sector, has been consistently growing via acquisition year on year. Selecting top talent from major players in the market, they have established a strong platform across finance, investment management, and asset performance.

They are currently looking for an experienced Senior Analyst to collaborate closely with property and asset managers to meet strategic goals. Reporting to the FP&A Manager you will focus on:

Lead asset-level budgeting and forecasting processes, including detailed financial modelling and variance analysis to support asset optimization

Partner with the Asset Manager and external property manager to monitor and enhance asset performance against asset business plans

Review monthly property financials from the property manager, analyse key performance drivers and provide commercial insights

Management of property trust account preparation including working with the external property manager and trust administrators

Calculation of property level distributable income and management of distributions

Prepare and provide insights into investor and co-investor reporting packs including financial analysis and performance commentary

Provide ad hoc financial analysis to support strategic initiatives and capital expenditure

You will be CA/CPA qualified with 6+ years of experience, including a minimum of 4 years in property or funds with exposure to analysis, asset/lease performance, budgeting/forecasting, and commercial business partnering. The ability to manage a portfolio, engaging comfortably and effectively with non-finance leaders, drive through performance, and operate commercially are all key.

Interested?

Please send your resume to chris.dubuis@lawsonelliott.com.au quoting reference CD17423.

High Growth Company

Employer of choice

Property/construction/land development

Due to continued exponential growth, a newly created position exists for an experienced analyst with a property/land development and/or construction background. The position will involve delivering strategic and operational insights to support planning, execution and delivery of major development and capital projects, bridging the gap between project teams, finance and senior leadership. You will analyse project feasibilities, track progress, manage risk and identify opportunities to improve efficiencies and add value. Our ideal candidate will combine strong analytical capabilities with a solid understanding of project life cycles, financial modelling and stakeholder communication.

Responsibilities

Project feasibility and business case support

Project performance tracking

Stakeholder engagement and communication

Process improvement and risk management

Tooling and data analytics

Required Qualifications and Skills

Bachelor's degree in Finance, Business, Engineering, Property or related field

3-5 years' experience in a business analysis, commercial or project support role

Understanding of project life cycles, in property or capital intensive industries.

Strong analytical, financial modelling and data interpretation skills.

Proficiency in Excel and project reporting tools (eg PowerBI and Tableau)

Strong communication skills, with the ability to influence and collaborate with teams across the business.

Preferred Qualifications and Skills

Experience in property development, infrastructure or construction projects

Familiar with project management methodologies

Knowledge of planning and approvals processes for developments (eg. permits, zoning, stakeholder engagement)

Proficient with project management systems such as Estate Master or equivalent

Don't miss this opportunity to be part of a vibrant and growing team, with massive growth expected over the next 5 years. Please only apply if you have relevant experience.

PLEASE NOTE: Trend Personnel is the exclusive recruiter for this employer. Direct applications or resumes referred by other recruiters will be deemed as unsolicited and will not be considered.

Ad Text:
Our client is a large NSW government department that provides extensive education services

They are at the forefront of digital reinvention; leveraging artificial intelligence to revolutionise education

Role Description:

The Senior AI Officer will support the Department’s AI governance and assurance activities by supporting the review and assessment of Artificial Intelligence Assessment Framework (AIAF) submissions.

The role focuses on ensuring AI initiatives are assessed consistently, proportionately and in line with NSW Government requirements; providing clear advice to decision makers and supporting safe, ethical and compliant AI adoption across the Department

This role does not deliver AI solutions; it provides assurance, risk assessment and expert advice.

Responsibilities:

Review Artificial Intelligence Assessment Framework (AIAF) submissions for completeness, quality and alignment with NSW Government requirements.
Assess AI initiatives against AIAF risk domains, working with the SME panel on ethics, fairness, privacy, security, transparency and accountability
Identify gaps, inconsistencies and risk issues - providing clear, actionable feedback to submitters.
Assess risk ratings and recommended assurance pathways based on scale, context and impact
Support the refinement of intake practices, systems and procedures to streamline AI requests and improve the quality of information 
Contribute to briefings, reports and summaries for governance forums and senior decision-makers.
Ensure alignment of AIAF assessments with the Digital Assurance Framework (DAF), NSW AI Ethics Principles, and relevant SMEs in privacy, cyber security and data.
Support consistent application of AI governance across corporate and school-based initiatives
Maintain alignment between AI risk management, departmental strategy and emerging AI opportunities
Skills and Experience

Essential

Demonstrated experience reviewing or assuring AI systems, digital solutions or data driven technologies.
Experience applying governance or assurance frameworks in a complex organisation or government environment.
Ability to assess technical and non-technical risks and communicate clearly with non specialist audiences
Strong written and verbal communication / documentation skills
Proven ability to liaise with technical and business stakeholders
Desirable

Familiarity with the NSW AIAF, DAF or equivalent government frameworks.
Experience with privacy impact assessments or technology assurance processes.
Understanding of AI use in education or public sector service delivery contexts
 Consultant: Colin Massey

Keywords: Artificial Intelligence, AI, NSW government, education, Artificial Intelligence Assessment Framework (AIAF), Digital Assurance Framework (DAF), NSW AI Ethics Principles, assurance, risk assessment, governance
